PRT101H1-F-20259.courseDescription: Introductory course to Portuguese for students with no previous knowledge of this language or advanced proficiency in Spanish. Taught in English and Portuguese.

PRT120H1-S-20261.courseDescription: Introduction to the Portuguese language for speakers of Spanish. Development of listening, speaking, reading, and writing skills with an emphasis on communication, and an overview of basic grammatical structures and building of vocabulary. Presentation of cultural aspects of the Portuguese-speaking world.
PRT120H1-S-20261.prerequisite: Native or advanced knowledge of Spanish, SPA320Y1/ SPA302H1 for non-native speakers of Spanish; no previous knowledge of Portuguese.
PRT120H1-S-20261.exclusion: PRT100Y1, PRT120Y1, PRT201H1, PRT202H1, PRT205H1, PRT219Y1, PRT219H1, PRT220Y1, PRT301H1, PRT302H1, PRT320Y1, PRT420Y1, PRT420H1

PRT201H1-F-20259.courseDescription: This course expands the linguistic repertoire of learners beyond basic structures by offering a review of grammar at an intermediate level. Introduction to authentic cultural materials from the Portuguese-speaking world with practice designed to build vocabulary, and to improve oral and written expression. Taught in Portuguese with occasional English.
PRT201H1-F-20259.prerequisite: PRT100Y1/ PRT102H1/ PRT120Y1/ PRT120H1 or placement test
PRT201H1-F-20259.exclusion: PRT202H1, PRT205H1, PRT219Y1, PRT219H1, PRT220Y1, PRT301H1, PRT302H1, PRT320Y1, PRT420Y1, PRT420H1

PRT202H1-S-20261.courseDescription: This course continues to expand the linguistic repertoire of learners to a high intermediate level, expanding the use of authentic cultural materials from the Portuguese-speaking world and promoting increased development of vocabulary, and oral and written expression. Taught in Portuguese with occasional English.
PRT202H1-S-20261.exclusion: PRT205H1, PRT219Y1, PRT219H1, PRT220Y1, PRT301H1, PRT302H1, PRT320Y1, PRT420Y1, PRT420H1

enrollmentControls.primaryOrgName: John H. Daniels Faculty of Architecture, Landscape, & Design

PRT205H1-F-20259.courseDescription: For students who have had exposure to spoken Portuguese in an informal context (living in a Portuguese speaking country, or in a Portuguese speaking family) but little to no exposure to written Portuguese. Besides reviewing English/Portuguese spelling differences, written and spoken registers of Portuguese, and basic aspects of the grammatical system, the course (1) provides students with the essential understanding of Portuguese grammatical system; (2) builds their vocabulary; and (3) trains them to express themselves formally in both spoken and written Portuguese. Taught in English and Portuguese.
PRT205H1-F-20259.prerequisite: Basic to relatively high ability to speak and understand Portuguese, limited or no formal education in Portuguese, or placement test.
PRT205H1-F-20259.exclusion: PRT100Y1, PRT101H1, PRT102H1, PRT120Y1, PRT120H1, PRT201H1, PRT202H1, PRT219Y1, PRT219H1, PRT220Y1, PRT301H1, PRT302H1, PRT320Y1, PRT420H1, PRT420Y1

PRT250H1-S-20261.courseTitle: Introduction to the Cultures of the Portuguese-Speaking World
PRT250H1-S-20261.courseDescription: A survey of historical and cultural trends in the Portuguese-speaking world, from colonial past to the present. (Offered in alternate years; taught in English)

enrollmentControls.primaryOrgName: John H. Daniels Faculty of Architecture, Landscape, & Design

PRT301H1-F-20259.courseDescription: Intensive practice in written and oral Portuguese for the student with advanced proficiency in the language. Selective review of grammar with emphasis on complex language structures. Taught in Portuguese.
PRT301H1-F-20259.prerequisite: PRT202H1/ PRT205H1/ PRT219Y1/ PRT219H1/ PRT220Y1 or placement test

enrollmentControls.primaryOrgName: John H. Daniels Faculty of Architecture, Landscape, & Design

PRT302H1-S-20261.courseDescription: This course continues to improve written and oral proficiency for the student with advanced proficiency in Portuguese, offering a selective review of grammar with emphasis on the complex sentence. Taught in Portuguese.

enrollmentControls.primaryOrgName: John H. Daniels Faculty of Architecture, Landscape, & Design

PRT358H1-F-20259.courseDescription: Exploration of cultural topics relevant to the Portuguese-speaking world. Examples include: Brazilian Popular Music, Soccer and Society, Luso-Afro-Brazilian Environmental Narratives, and Lusophone Women Writers. Students can enroll in this course multiple times, as long as the topic of the course is different. For any questions, please reach out to the Associate Chairs of Undergraduate Studies or Portuguese Studies. Taught in Portuguese.
PRT358H1-F-20259.prerequisite: PRT258H1, PRT120H1/ PRT205H1/ PRT219Y1/ PRT219H1 or Portuguese placement test

enrollmentControls.primaryOrgName: John H. Daniels Faculty of Architecture, Landscape, & Design

PRT364H1-F-20259.courseDescription: An overview of the varieties of Portuguese spoken in four continents (Europe, South America, Africa, Asia) and a discussion of the structural similarities and differences between the two most extensively studied varieties: European and Brazilian Portuguese. Analysis of linguistic variation in contemporary Portuguese in terms of phonetics, syntax and lexicon. (Offered in alternate years.)
PRT364H1-F-20259.prerequisite: PRT202H1/ PRT205H1/ PRT219Y1/ PRT219H1/ PRT120Y1/ PRT220Y1 or Portuguese placement test.

enrollmentControls.primaryOrgName: John H. Daniels Faculty of Architecture, Landscape, & Design

PRT470H1-S-20261.courseTitle: Acquisition of Portuguese as a Second Language
PRT470H1-S-20261.courseDescription: Invites critical reflection about the acquisition of Portuguese as a second language. Analyzes phonological, morphosyntactic, semantic and lexical aspects in the linguistic performance of bilingual speakers, and of learners of Portuguese as a second language. (Offered in alternate years)
PRT470H1-S-20261.prerequisite: PRT202H1/ PRT205H1/ PRT219Y1/ PRT219H1/ PRT220Y1 or Portuguese placement test.
